<HEADLINE>
<P>
OBITUARIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Terrence Clancy; Former President of Wine Alliance 
</P>
<P>
 Terrence Clancy, 60, former president of the Wine Alliance and a member of the 
executive committee of the Wine Institute. A native of Los Angeles and graduate 
of Occidental College, Clancy entered the wine business with E&J Gallo in 
1957.In 1981, he was hired as president of Callaway Vineyards in Temecula. In 
1988, Britain's Allied Lyons PLC appointed Clancy as president of its North 
American wine division and head of four wineries: Callaway, Clos du Bois, Atlas 
Peak and William Hill. On Tuesday in San Francisco of cardiac disease. 
</P>
<P>
 * Elliott William Henry Jr.; Public Relations Executive for ABC 
</P>
<P>
 Elliott William Henry Jr., 79, pioneer broadcasting public relations 
executive. After graduating from Beloit College in Wisconsin, Henry worked 
briefly for Howard Mayer Public Relations in Chicago. In 1943, he joined the 
Blue Network, which later became American Broadcasting. He moved to Los Angeles 
in 1960 when he was named vice president for West Coast public relations of the 
ABC Television Network. Henry retired in 1975. During his tenure, national 
television writers consistently voted his department the best of all television 
public relations programs. On Dec. 4 in Vancouver, Wash. 
</P>
</TEXT>
