<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; SCHOOL TRUSTEES TO MEET ON CAMPUSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In an attempt to increase parents' involvement in school issues, the Oxnard 
School District Board of Trustees has agreed to hold four of its next 12 
meetings at school sites across the city. 
</P>
<P>
 The board, which voted unanimously for the project Wednesday, will have its 
first meeting at a school as early as February, said district Supt.Bernard 
Korenstein. 
</P>
<P>
 Although it will cost $160 each time they move microphones and other 
electronic equipment from the district office in downtown Oxnard to the school 
sites, the effort is worthwhile, Korenstein said. 
</P>
<P>
 "A large number of people have shown an interest in knowing what is going on 
in the district and the schools. However, it's not always convenient for them 
to come to our office," he said. "So we thought, 'Why not bring the meeting to 
the community?' " 
</P>
<P>
 Korenstein said the goal is to have the meetings at schools in different parts 
of the city. The schools will notify parents when the meetings are scheduled. 
</P>
<P>
 To facilitate parents' attendance, the district plans to offer baby-sitting 
services. 
</P>
<P>
 Parents who need baby sitters must sign up in advance. CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</TEXT>
