<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SAN CLEMENTE; PHOTO OPPORTUNITY WITH SURFIN' SANTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 There are a multitude of photo opportunities with St. Nick, but where other 
than San Clemente can Surfin' Santa be found? 
</P>
<P>
 In a city that is one of Southern California's surfing hot spots, people can 
have their picture taken with Santa and a surfboard against a rolling ocean 
background today from 10 a.m. to 3 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 "We have a jolly and slightly rotund teacher who has enthusiastically 
volunteered to be Santa," said Christopher Cairns, principal of San Clemente 
High."He's dressed as Santa with sunglasses and a surfboard." 
</P>
<P>
 Santa will be at a Lucky's grocery store, 804 Avenida Pico. 
</P>
<P>
 The cost is $2.50 and proceeds will benefit the San Clemente High School pep 
squad. 
</P>
<P>
 Surfin' Santa has visited the San Clemente High School campus this week, 
taking photos with students. 
</P>
<P>
 Cairns said response from the student body has been enthusiastic. 
</P>
<P>
 The surfing theme makes sense, he said, because "we live in Southern 
California and San Clemente High School is a perennial powerhouse in surfing. 
And it's fun." FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
