<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; NEW PUBLIC WORKS DIRECTOR HAS O.C. TIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DEBRA CANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city has hired a new public works director. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council recently approved City Administrator Michael T. Uberuaga's 
selection of Les Jones.Since 1991, Jones was city manager of Los Altos Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Jones, who began his public service career in 1976 for the city of Garden 
Grove, will begin with the city on Jan. 9. His salary will be $8,100 a month. 
Jones holds a bachelor of arts degree in public administration from Cal State 
Fullerton and has done graduate studies at Cal State Long Beach and San Diego 
State University. 
</P>
<P>
 He also has worked for the city of Coronado, in San Diego County, where he was 
assistant to the city manager and later, director of public works. DEBRA CANO 
</P>
