<HEADLINE>
<P>
ENCINO HANUKKAH SHOW WAS WELL DISCIPLINED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 We don't know what program your reporter saw on Friday night, ("Lighthearted 
Celebration of Hanukkah," Valley Focus, Dec. 3) but apparently it was different 
from the one we attended at Valley Beth Shalom in Encino. 
</P>
<P>
 We take strong exception to the statement that the children "fidgeted with 
their costumes, fumbled their choreography and dissolved into chaos at the end 
of each song."On the contrary, our observation and comments immediately 
following the program were how wonderfully well they (the 6- and 7-year-olds) 
knew all the words of the various songs and how well-disciplined their 
performance was throughout the program. We saw no chaos; keep in mind, this was 
not a professional Las Vegas production number. 
</P>
<P>
 This is another example of how and why we have become cynics and skeptics of 
reporting on any and all subjects by the media. 
</P>
<P>
 One more positive note, we would very much like to thank you for covering this 
event, and for conveying to the community the basic message of Hanukkah. 
</P>
<P>
 MAURY ABRAMS, FRANCINE ABRAMS, Encino 
