<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWPORT BEACH SEX ATTACK MAY BE TIED TO OTHERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man who may have been involved in two other attacks tried to rob and 
sexually assault a woman early Friday but fled when her roommate came home, 
investigators said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man entered the woman's Colton Street residence through an unlocked front 
door about 3:45 a.m., Police Sgt. Andy Gonis said.He was armed with a gun and 
threatened to rob and rape the woman, Gonis said. 
</P>
<P>
 But before the assailant could carry out his threats, the woman's roommate 
entered the residence and surprised him, Gonis said. The man fled. 
</P>
<P>
 The incident was similar to two previous attacks, one that occurred Nov. 29 on 
38th Street in Newport Beach and another Dec. 3 at an undisclosed address in 
Costa Mesa, Gonis said. Police in both cities are advising residents to keep 
their doors and windows locked at all times. 
</P>
<P>
 The assailant was described by police as an African American, 5 feet, 8 inches 
tall and about 190 pounds. He is stocky with short, black hair and may have a 
small mustache, Gonis said. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with information should call (800) 550-NBPD or (714) 754-5255. 
</P>
</TEXT>
