EAST VALLEY FOCUS: VAN NUYS; QUAKE CENTER OPENS TO HEAR COMPLAINTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Contractors State License Board opened a new Earthquake Response Center in 
its Van Nuys district office Friday to deal specifically with complaints about 
contractors doing quake repairs. 
</P>
<P>
 The number of complaints has risen dramatically since victims of the 
Northridge earthquake began receiving insurance payments and federal funds to 
repair their homes, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 With the additional office, people can expect investigations into complaints 
to begin within two weeks of their first call, said Sam Haynes, a spokesman for 
the board. 
</P>
<P>
 He recommended that people have the full name and license number of the 
contractor when calling in a complaint. 
</P>
