<HEADLINE>
<P>
ACCUSED KILLER OF WOODLAND HILLS MAN MAY FACE 2ND MURDER CHARGE; CRIME: POLICE 
SAY THEY ARE '99% SURE' BODY FOUND NEAR CASTAIC IS THAT OF A CHICAGO WOMAN LAST 
SEEN WITH JACK ALAN GOGA. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE TAMAKI and NICHOLAS RICCARDI, TIMES STAFF WRITERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police said Friday they will seek a new murder charge against Jack Alan Goga 
-- who this week was charged in the death of a Woodland Hills man -- after 
tentatively identifying a body found in June as that of a Chicago woman who was 
last seen in Goga's company. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles Police Detective Rick Swanston said authorities are "99% sure" 
that a body found June 14 near Castaic is that of Digna Adames, 25, who 
disappeared in mid-June after traveling to Los Angeles with Goga. 
</P>
<P>
 Goga, 50, who is being held in police custody in Michigan, has already been 
charged with the murder of Charles (Chick) Evans, whose body was found in his 
Woodland Hills home on Dec. 7. 
</P>
<P>
 Police say they have tentatively identified the body found near North Ridge 
and Lake Hughes roads as Adames after viewing coroner's photographs of bodies 
found around the time Adames disappeared. 
</P>
<P>
 Adames left a 7-year-old son in Chicago in May to travel to Los Angeles with 
Goga after the former Motown producer promised her a recording contract, family 
members said. 
</P>
<P>
 Adames would call home frequently but the calls stopped after June 10, her 
father's birthday, said Adames' sister Rosa Medino in a telephone interview 
from Chicago. 
</P>
<P>
 Adames was reported missing in early July, and her family spent months 
agonizing over her fate. 
</P>
<P>
 "I just hope he gets what he deserves," Medino said of Goga on Friday. Of her 
sister, Medino said, "We just want to get the remains and bury her." 
</P>
<P>
 Police say they believe Goga killed Evans, 60, after the Woodland Hills man 
tried to get his house guest to leave. 
</P>
</TEXT>
