<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY IN BANKRUPTCY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Contributing to today's coverage of Orange County's financial troubles were: 
staff writers Leslie Berkman, Jeff Brazil, Anna Cekola, Greg Johnson, Matt 
Lait, Mark Landsbaum, Eric Lichtblau, Julie Marquis, Martin Miller, Tom 
Petruno, Mark Platte, H.G. Reza, Lee Romney, Rebecca Trounson, Debora Vrana, 
Tracy Weber, Dan Weikel, Jodi Wilgoren, Chris Woodyard. 
</P>
<P>
 Also contributing were photographer Geraldine Wilkins and correspondents Jeff 
Bean, Bill Billiter, Debra Cano, Leslie Earnest, Bert Eljera, Alan Eyerly, Lynn 
Franey, Shelby Grad, Hope Hamashige, Mimi Ko, Russ Loar, Frank Messina, Jon 
Nalick and Tom Ragan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA121794-0190 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 109009 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
December 17, 1994, Saturday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
