<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE WOMEN'S BASKETBALL; SKEHAN PROVIDES SADDLEBACK WITH FINAL 
MARGIN OF SAFETY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Maureen Skehan's free throw with a second left helped Saddleback defeat Los 
Angeles Trade Tech, 48-47, Friday in the first round of the Orange Coast 
Christmas Classic. 
</P>
<P>
 Skehan's free throw gave Saddleback a four-point lead and the Gauchos didn't 
contest Julia Sanchez's shot as time ran out. 
</P>
<P>
 Skehan finished with nine points. Shannon Nelson scored a game-high 20 points 
and had 12 rebounds for Saddleback (5-2), which plays Chaffey in one semifinal 
at 5:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 In other tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
 Chaffey 75, Fullerton 58 -- Nicole deBruijn scored 18 points for Fullerton 
despite making only four of 16 shots from the field. Three of the baskets were 
three-pointers and she made seven of nine free throws. Fullerton plays Los 
Angeles Trade Tech in a consolation game at 1:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles Valley 81, Orange Coast 67 -- America Robledo scored 19 points, 
but Orange Coast was too far behind at the half to rally. Los Angeles Valley 
(8-3) opened a 39-22 lead at the break. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles Valley scored the first six points of the second half to open a 
45-22 lead. Orange Coast got within 10 with about nine minutes left but got no 
closer. 
</P>
<P>
 Jamie Shine had 12 points for Orange Coast (11-3), which plays El Camino at 
3:30 p.m. in a consolation game. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles Valley plays Southwestern at 7:30 p.m. in a semifinal. 
</P>
