<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; TRABUCO HILLS MANAGES TO RALLY, OVERTAKE CAPISTRANO 
VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Trabuco Hills played well in the fourth quarter to pull away from Capistrano 
Valley, 53-39, Friday in one semifinal of the Bolsa Grande tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mustangs led by five after three quarters, but outscored Capistrano 
Valley, 20-11, in the fourth quarter. LaShieka Henderson led Trabuco Hills 
(7-2) with 18 points and 15 rebounds. Dyanna Hatch added 11. 
</P>
<P>
 Trabuco Hills plays Montebello Cantwell in the championship game at 7 p.m. 
Capistrano Valley plays Westminster for third place at 5:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 In consolation round: 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente 58, Tustin 52 -- Emily Ela scored 18 points to lead San Clemente 
in consolation action. The Tritons (4-5) will play Magnolia at 4 p.m. today for 
fifth place. Katie Scheuerman scored 26 points for Tustin (5-5). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Orange Lutheran Pride Invitational: 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Lutheran 51, Riverside Woodcrest Christian 36 -- Orange Lutheran's Liz 
Pappas led with eight points. Orange Lutheran (4-2) will take on Whittier 
Christian for the tournament championship at 8:30 tonight. Shannon Hanks scored 
12 points for Woodcrest Christian (5-3), which will take on Century at 6:30 
p.m. for third place. 
</P>
<P>
 Whittier Christian 56, Century 40 -- Alana Kempton had 15 points and 10 
rebounds, Faye Tsiramanes had 14 points and 12 rebounds and Kristi Ralston had 
10 points and 10 rebounds for Whittier Christian (6-2) in one semifinal. Addy 
and Nina Alexander each had 11 points for Century (5-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Liberty Christian 26, Connelly 20 -- Lisa Winters scored eight of her 12 
points in the fourth quarter for Liberty Christian (5-2), which shutout 
Connelly, 10-0, in the fourth quarter for the consolation win. Georgina 
Cervantes led Connelly (1-4) with eight points. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Valley Christian Tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Los Alamitos 43, Lakewood Mayfair 23 -- Sarah Nunley and Jessica Peterson each 
scored eight points for Los Alamitos (4-3). 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague games: 
</P>
<P>
 Sonora 58, City of Industry Workman 31 -- Aiyanna Nash scored 22 points and 
had five assists to lead Sonora (2-4). Kristi DeOliva had 14 rebounds and Mary 
Rubio had nine rebounds for the Raiders. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange 48, Anaheim 38 -- Charlene Conley had 17 points and 18 rebounds to lead 
Orange (3-5), which led, 25-15, at the half. 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley Christian 63, Southern California Christian 15 -- Jessica 
Olivier had 19 points and 18 rebounds and Danielle Pierce added 13 points for 
Capistrano Valley Christian (4-4), which led, 34-1, at the half. 
