<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEACE FUND FOR KIDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 My wife and I were deeply touched by a story in Liz Smith's Nov. 25 column 
dealing with Judy Collins' recent visit to Yugoslavia for UNICEF. 
</P>
<P>
 It was during this visit that she learned of the grotesque "flower mines," of 
which children are the principal targets, and which have inspired her new 
Christmas album, "Song for Sarajevo." 
</P>
<P>
 A telephone number -- (800) FOR-KIDS -- was listed in Smith's report for 
anyone interested in helping the children of Sarajevo, especially this holiday 
season. 
</P>
<P>
 We called the number listed, which is a regional office for UNICEF; but for 
more information on the Judy Collins/Sarajevo project, we were directed to 
UNICEF in New York City. 
</P>
<P>
 For others who may wish to support this project, contributions should be 
addressed to: "I Dream of Peace" Fund, U.S. Committee for UNICEF, 333 E. 38th 
St., New York, N.Y. 10016, Attn: Ms. Kelly Faulkner. 
</P>
<P>
 BARRY MICKLEWRIGHT 
</P>
<P>
 Palm Desert 
</P>
</TEXT>
